  "@type": "SolutionRecord",
  "@id": "ocp:github/tidwall--tile38",
  "meta": {
    "title": "The tile38 shell connects to localhost:9851",
    "description": "Real-time Geospatial and Geofencing",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-11T04:44:46.729Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-11T04:44:46.729Z",
    "keywords": [
      "database",
      "geo",
      "geofences",
      "geospatial",
      "index",
      "location",
      "spatial"
    ],
    "license": "MIT"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "- Spatial index with [search](#searching) methods such as Nearby, Within, and Intersects.\n- Realtime [geofencing](#geofencing) through [webhooks](https://tile38.com/commands/sethook) or [pub/sub channels](#pubsub-channels).\n- Object types of [lat/lon](#latlon-point), [bbox](#bounding-box), [Geohash](#geohash), [GeoJSON](#geojson), [QuadKey](#quadkey), and [XYZ tile](#xyz-tile).\n- Support for lots of [Clients Libraries](#tile38-client-libraries) written in many different languages.\n- Variety of protocols, including [http](#http) (curl), [websockets](#websockets), [telnet](#telnet), and the [Redis RESP](https://redis.io/topics/protocol).\n- Server responses are [RESP](https://redis.io/topics/protocol) or [JSON](https://www.json.org).\n- Full [command line interface](#cli).\n- Leader / follower [replication](#replication).\n- In-memory database that persists on disk.",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
  "domains": [
    "data-management",
    "lang:go"
  ],
